{"title_page": "Oru Kal Oru Kannadi", "text_new": "{{About|the Tamil film|the song|Oru Kal Oru Kannadi (song)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Oru Kal Oru Kannadi\n| image          = OKOK.jpg\n| alt            = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[M. Rajesh]]\n| producer       = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]]\n| writer         = M. Rajesh\n| starring       = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]] <br />[[Hansika Motwani]]<br />[[Narayan Lucky]]<br />[[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]]<br />[[Jangiri Madhumitha]]\n| music          = [[Harris Jayaraj]]\n| cinematography = [[Balasubramaniem]]\n| editing        = [[Vivek Harshan]]\n| studio         = [[Red Giant Movies]]\n| distributor    = [[Red Giant Movies]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2012|4|13|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 166 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|130|m|year=2012}}<ref name=\"Sify\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil-cinema-2012-half-yearly-report-jan-1-june-30-news-tamil-mhhsLzccaaa.html |title=Tamil Cinema 2012- Half Yearly Report (Jan 1-June 30)|publisher=Sify |date=2012-07-07 |accessdate=2012-11-09}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|420|m|year=2012}}<ref name=\"Sify\" />\n}}\n\n'''''Oru Kal Oru Kannadi''''' ({{lit|One Stone, One Mirror}}) abbreviated as '''''OKOK''''' is a [[Tamil films of 2012|2012]] [[Tamil language|Tamil]] [[romantic comedy]] film written and directed by [[M. Rajesh]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Anupama Subramanian DC chennai |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/udhay%E2%80%99s-new-look-okok-912 |title=Udhay\u2019s new look in OKOK |publisher=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=2011-03-23 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> It stars producer [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]], in his acting debut, [[Hansika Motwani]] and [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]], whilst featuring [[Harris Jayaraj]]'s music and [[Balasubramaniem]]'s cinematography.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-17/news-interviews/28374647_1_harris-jayaraj-music-romantic-flick Jayaraj to give music for Rajesh's OKOK&nbsp;\u2013 Times Of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2011-01-17). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> The film was named after [[Oru Kal Oru Kannadi (song)|a song]] from the film ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'' (2009). Releasing on 13 April 2012, it opened to highly positive reviews and became a blockbuster.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-22/news-interviews/31378800_1_hansika-fee-oru-kal-oru-kannadi Hansika hikes her fee to 75 lakhs&nbsp;\u2013 Times Of India]. Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2012-04-22). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref><ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-22/news-interviews/31373320_1_tamil-bollywood-debut-film Oru Kal Oru Kannadi to be remade in Bollywood&nbsp;\u2013 Times Of India]. Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2012-04-22). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref><ref name=\"behindwoods1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-movies-may-14/oru-kal-oru-kannadi.html |title=Oru Kal Oru kannadi&nbsp;\u2014 Behindwoods.com&nbsp;\u2014 Tamil Top Ten Movies&nbsp;\u2014 Kalakalappu Vazhakku En 18/7 Leelai Ooh La La La Mattuthavani Mye Oru kal Oru kannadi Asthamanam Mazhaikalam 3 Karnan Meeravudan Krishnan Sooriya Nagaram Nandha Nandhitha Sevarkodi Naanga Aravaan Kaattu Puli Udumban Kadhalil Sodhapuvadhu Yeppadi Muppozhudhum Un Karpanaigal Mouna Guru kollaikaran Vettai Nanban Osthe Rajapattai Uchithanai Mukarnthal Mouna Guru Mambattiyan Velayudham 7aum Arivu Porali Mayakkam Enna |publisher=Behindwoods |date= |accessdate=2012-08-05}}</ref> It was eventually released in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''OK OK'' on 31 August 2012.\n\n== Plot ==\nOne morning in his house, Saravanan receives his ex-girlfriend Meera's wedding invitation. He and his friend Paarthasarathy aka Paartha leave for [[Pondicherry]] to attend the wedding via car. ''En route'', Saravanan recollects his past: He was a ruthless youth working in a film theatre with Paartha. He lives with his parents; his father, Varadharajan, who is educated and works as a college professor and his mother, Shenbagam, who is uneducated and is trying to pass an exam, just to get her college degree. One day in traffic, he sees Meera, a girl training to be an air hostess and [[Love at first sight|falls for her on site]]. He follows her to a cloth shop and also to her Air Hostess class. He saw her house and he and Partha go to her house, as Meera calls them. There, Meera threatens Saravanan by showing her father's photo, who is a Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), Mahendra Kumar. But still, Saravanan follows her and asks her to love him. Meera takes him to Mahendra Kumar's office and he asks Saravanan to stop following Meera. Meera tells Saravanan that she has some qualifications required by her lover like shaving regularly, dressing well, breaking his friendship with Paartha, coming on time, etc.  Saravanan tells this to Partha and Partha asks him if he or Meera is best for him. Saravanan tells him Meera is more important to him than Paartha, causing a break between Saravanan's and Paartha's friendship.\n\nLater, Saravanan joins Paartha's broken love and asks him to rejoin his love. Partha agrees and then they go to [[Mumbai]], following Meera in a flight. There, Meera alas tells him that she loves Saravanan. After some months, Meera calls Saravanan once, but he does not pick up the phone and tells Paartha that Meera is not his real love and it is all nothing, but a drama. But, he really said that for fun. But, Paartha had accidentally switched on the phone while Saravanan told him all this. Meera, mistaking him for intentionally misusing her, comes there and breaks their love. Now, at Pondicherry, during Meera's marriage, both Saravanan and Partha end up drunk and tell a small story, in a comical way describing the broken love of Saravanan and Meera. Just as the marriage is going to happen, Rajini Murugan, a local don, comes there with a pregnant girl and his girlfriend and reveals that Meera's groom has a girlfriend, who is pregnant by him and that the girl Rajini Murugan is with, is that girl. The groom admits to his mistake and reunites with his old girlfriend. Saravanan and Paartha walk off the marriage hall, just then Meera comes and hugs Saravanan, hence reuniting with him.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]] as Saravanan\n* [[Hansika Motwani]] as Meera\n* [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]] as Paartha\n* [[Narayan Lucky]] as Sanjay, Meera's Fianc\u00e9\n* [[Saranya Ponvannan]] as Shenbagam\n* [[Azhagam Perumal]] as Varadharajan\n* [[Sayaji Shinde]] as DC Mahendrakumar\n* [[Uma Padmanabhan]] as Gayathri\n* [[Jangiri Madhumitha]] as Jangiri\n* [[Swaminathan]] as Ulundurpettai Ulaganantha\n* [[Mahanadi Shankar]] as Traffic Police\n*[[Arya (actor)|Arya]] as Rajini Murugan (special appearance)\n* [[Andrea Jeremiah]] as Rajini Murugan's girlfriend [special appearce]\n* [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Jennifer (special appearance)\n* [[Dinesh Kumar (choreographer)|Dinesh Kumar]] (special appearance in the song \"Kadhal Oru\")<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xAfHFFi0O6E |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2014 Kaadhal Oru Video Udhayanidhi, Hansika |publisher=Youtube |date=16 December 2014 |accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nUdhayanidhi Stalin had bought the distribution rights of Rajesh's previous film ''[[Boss Engira Bhaskaran]]''.<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58980.html Red Giant acquires Boss Engira Bhaskaran&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil Movie News]. IndiaGlitz (2010-07-29). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> As the film emerged successful, Udhayanidhi decided to continue the collaboration, going on to play the lead role in the new project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chennai365.com/news/udhayanidhi-is-the-hero-for-director-rajesh/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=12 April 2012 |url-status=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100811210306/http://chennai365.com/news/udhayanidhi-is-the-hero-for-director-rajesh/ |archivedate=11 August 2010 }}. chennai365.com. June 2, 2010</ref>\n\nDuring the pre-production stage,  several actresses including [[Asin Thottumkal]] and [[Nayantara]] were approached to play the female lead but [[Hansika Motwani]] was eventually signed. The protagonist was revealed to be an unemployed youngster, as unofficial reports of a ticket collector and a band master were brushed aside.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/64612.html |title=Who is Udhayanidhi in 'OK OK'? |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-03-07 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] and [[Andrea Jeremiah]] were roped in to perform cameo roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/69565.html |title=Arya to do a cameo |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-08-08 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> Hansika was forced to learn [[Tamil language|Tamil]], for the director wanted her to speak fluently in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/73418.html |title=Hansika masters Tamil? |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-11-02 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> Rajesh planned to retain the same crew members from his first two ventures but since Udhayanidhi wanted [[Harris Jayaraj]] to score the music for his debut film, he was signed over Rajesh's usual associate [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], while the makers decided to proceed with Balasubramaniam as the cinematographer as [[Sakthi Saravanan]] was unavailable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-11-02/ok-ok-rajesh-08-03-11.html |title=Okok Shoot To Commence |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-03-08 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nA photo shoot for the film was held in February 2011 with the lead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-11-01/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-rajesh-07-02-11.html |title= Hansika OK OK |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-02-07 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> The shooting of the film began in March 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/64907.html |title=It's shooting time for 'OKOK' |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-03-16 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> Filming was held in [[Tidel Park]] and [[Old Mahabalipuram Road|Rajiv Gandhi Road]] in [[Chennai]] on 26 April. The car in which they drive to pondicherry was modified with power steering and other interesting elements. A pondicherry bar was setup in woodlands hotel campus.  In the song Azhage, which was totally shot in dubai, in between bgms were recreated in VGP beach and matched by art director [[Jacki]].<ref>[http://www.sify.com/movies/rajesh-s-nanbenda-becomes-okok-news-tamil-lbsjuleeaej.html?scategory=tamil Rajesh's Nanbenda becomes OKOK]. Sify.com (2011-01-19). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> Overseas shooting locations included Jordan and [[Abu Dhabi]], where the film's team flew over to shoot a song in December 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/okok-team-flies-to-jordan-news-tamil-lmriPSiebde.html |title=OKOK team flies to Jordan |publisher=[[Sify]] |date=2011-12-17 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-11-04/udayanidhi-stalin-oru-kal-oru-kannadi-27-12-11.html |title=Ok Ok Dubai Schedule Completed |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-12-27 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> Some shots were canned at the PVR theater in Ampa Mall, Aminjikarai. Hansika Motwani and Saranya were spotted doing a scene together in the theater.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-11-04/okok-udhayanidhi-stalin-28-03-11.html |title=Hansika Motwani Spotted At Pvr Theaters |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-03-28 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> In the second schedule, director Rajesh shot a scene on Udayanidhi Stalin, Azhagam Perumal and Saranya Ponvannan at [[KK Nagar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/may-11-03/udayanidhi-stalin-hansika-motwani-21-05-11.html |title=Ok Ok Shooting Wrapped Up |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-05-21 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> During a schedule, Santhanam was hospitalized due to illness, delaying the shoot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-11-01/santhanam-okok-05-04-11.html |title=Santhanam Is Possessed! |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-04-05 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]]. Oru Kal Oru Kannadi was released on 13 April 2012 in Tamil as a [[Tamil New Year]] release and on 31 August 2012 in Telugu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.moviegalleri.net/2012/03/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-movie-release-date-on-april-13th-friday.html |title=OKOK Movie Release date on April 13th}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Oru Kal Oru Kannadi\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Harris Jayaraj]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|4 March 2012}}\n| recorded   = 2012\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 25:35\n| language   = [[Tamil (language)|Tamil]]\n| label      = [[Sony Music India]]\n| producer   = Harris Jayaraj\n| prev_title = [[Nanban (2012 film)|Nanban]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Maattrraan]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n}}\n\nThe album features five songs,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/78907.html |title='OKOK' track details |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-03-05 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> composed by [[Harris Jayaraj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-11-04/ok-ok-rajesh-25-02-11.html |title=On Harris Replacing Yuvan |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-02-25 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> The composing sessions took place in [[Singapore]] and [[Ooty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/64808.html |title=Harris in Singapore. OKOK |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-03-12 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-11-02/okok-udhayanidhi-stalin-12-03-11.html |title=Harris Jeyaraj In Singapore |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-03-12 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> The audio launch was held at the Sathyam Cinemas on 4 March 2012. Actors Karthi, Surya, Jeeva and Arya were present at the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/78955.html |title=Suriya unveils 'Oru Kal Oru Kannadi' music |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-03-06 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> A three-minute trailer and song sequences was screened for the guests and media people as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamil.oneindia.in/movies/news/2012/02/okok-music-from-march-5-aid0136.html |title=OKOK music from March 5 &#124; \u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd 5-\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b87\u0b9a\u0bc8!&nbsp;\u2013 Oneindia Tamil |publisher=Tamil.oneindia.in |date= |accessdate=2012-02-23}}</ref>\n\nThe soundtrack received generally positive reviews. Behindwoods.com claimed that it \"definitely has a few like-able singalongs to keep the audio outlets happy\", providing a rating of 3/5.<ref>[http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-music-reviews/review-1/mar-12-01/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-music-review.html Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Music Review&nbsp;\u2013 Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Music Review]. Behindwoods.com. Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> The Song Venam Machan Venam became an Instant hit and topped the chart for several weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.paatuvarigal.com/2015/01/venam-machan-venam-song-lyrics-from-oru.html|title=Venam Machan Venam Song Lyrics from Oru Kal Oru Kannadi|work=Paatuvarigal \u2013 Tamil Song Lyrics|access-date=2018-05-30}}</ref> Indiaglitz.com mentioned that the composer had \"fulfilled the director's expectations, as the songs strike a chord during the first-listen itself. 'Oru Kal Oru Kannadi' music album celebrates love and reflects youngsters, like the previous films of Rajesh.\"<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/12922.html Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Music Review songs lyrics]. IndiaGlitz (2012-03-07). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| extra_column     = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics       = [[Na. Muthukumar]]\n| total_length     = 25:35\n| headline= Track-List<ref>{{cite web |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi - All Songs - Download or Listen Free - Saavn |url=https://www.saavn.com/album/oru-kal-oru-kannadi/LJr5u9Xt-Kw_ |accessdate=4 November 2018 |date=5 March 2012}}</ref>\n| length1       = 6:04\n| title1        = Kaadhal Oru\n| extra1        = [[Aalap Raju]], [[Vedala Hemachandra]], [[Sunitha Sarathy]]\n| length2       = 5:54\n| title2        = Azhage Azhage\n| extra2        = Mukesh, [[Srimathumitha]]\n| length3       = 4:43\n| title3        = Akila Akila\n| extra3        = Aalap Raju, [[Chinmayi]], Sharmila\n| length4       = 3:43\n| title4        = Adada Oru\n| extra4        = [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| length5       = 5:11\n| title5        = Venaam Machaan\n| extra5        = [[Naresh Iyer]], [[Velmurugan]]\n}}\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Ok Ok\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Harris Jayaraj]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2012\n| recorded   = 2012\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 25:44\n| language   = [[Telugu (language)|Telugu]]\n| label      = [[Sony Music India]]\n| producer   = Harris Jayaraj\n}}\n{{track listing\n| extra_column     = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics       = [[Bhuvanachandra]]\n| total_length     =  25:44\n| headline = Telugu Track-List<ref>{{cite web |title=Ok Ok - All Songs - Download or Listen Free - Saavn |url=https://www.saavn.com/album/ok-ok/53mw6rQvL4Q_ |accessdate=4 November 2018 |date=8 July 2012}}</ref>\n| length1       = 6:06\n| title1        = Just Like\n| extra1        = Aalap Raju, Vedala Hemachandra, Sunitha Sarathy\n| length2       = 5:59\n| title2        = Areree Areree\n| extra2        = Mukesh, Srimathumitha\n| length3       = 4:42\n| title3        = Akila Akila\n| extra3        = Aalap Raju, [[Chinmayi]], Sharmila\n| length4       = 3:48\n| title4        = Kalala Oka Devathe\n| extra4        = Karthik\n| length5       = 5:09\n| title5        = Vaddura Maavaa\n| extra5        = Naresh Iyer, Velmurugan\n}}\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Critical reception ===\n''Oru Kal Oru Kannadi'' received positive reviews and became a blockbuster at the box office. ''[[Sify]] ''called it a \"rollicking comedy\", stating: \"If all you're looking for is a relaxed time at the movies, then, this is Good Fun. Go with your buddies,  you'll laugh till you have tears in your eyes\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi is Rollicking comedy|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-review-tamil-14996316.html|publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' rated it 3.5 out of 5 and said: \"M Rajesh is a rarity in Tamil cinema. How else does one explain sitting through almost a three-hour-long movie without realising the passage of time?\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Oru-Kal-Oru-Kannadi/movie-review/12659866.cms |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Review |publisher=[[The Times of India]] |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}{{Rating|3.5|5}}</ref> ''IndiaGlitz'' said \"Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2013 Humour At Its Best!\" and wrote that it was a \"clean and convincing film that makes you laugh every minute\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/12922.html |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2013 Humour At Its Best! |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> ''Behindwoods.com'' rated the film 3 out of 5, stating: \"OKOK double OK\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/apr-12-02/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-review.html |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Review |publisher=Behindwoods |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}{{Rating|3|5}}</ref> Oneindia stated that the film \"may not have a great storyline, but watching the film is worth every penny\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/reviews/2012/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-review-140412.html |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2013 Review |publisher=Oneindia |date=|accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> Rohit Ramachandran of Nowrunning.com stated that it was \"by no means a meaningful film experience, but it is a portal for popcorn escapism\".<ref>[http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/8703/tamil/oru-kal-oru-kannadi/3665/review.htm Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Review&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil Movie Review by Rohit Ramachandran]. Nowrunning.com (2012-04-14). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> Pavithra Srinivasan from [[Rediff.com]] rated it 2 out of 5 and said: \"''OKOK'' is a slightly torturous friendship story of two guys and that's pretty much it\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-oru-kal-oru-kannaadi-is-tortuous/20120413.htm |title=Review: Oru Kal, Oru Kannaadi is tortuous&nbsp;|publisher=Rediff|date=|accessdate=14 April 2012}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\n''Oru Kal Oru Kannadi'' opened in more than 300 screens, with an average of 95 per cent theatre occupancy in urban regions.<ref name=\"behindwoods1\" /> The film began to collect even larger sums of revenue in the next four continuous weeks, acquiring a total of {{INR}}15.09 crore in a matter of 25 days in [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"behindwoods1\" /><ref name=\"indiaglitz1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/82110.html |title=Karthi&nbsp;\u2014 Kajal team up again? - Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-05-14 |accessdate=2012-08-05}}</ref> The film claimed top spot for more than a month at the Chennai box office. Trade pundits declared the film's collections as impressive.<ref name=\"behindwoods1\" /><ref name=\"indiaglitz1\" /><ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-23/news-interviews/31386464_1_comedy-films-scripts-rights | work=The Times Of India | title=OK OK remake rights becomes hot}}</ref> Taken with a budget of {{INR}}13 crore it grossed around {{INR}}42 crore worldwide.<ref name=\"Sify\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|2359201}}\n\n{{M. Rajesh}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Tamil film scores by Harris Jayaraj]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Chennai]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Puducherry]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Dubai]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Jordan]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Abu Dhabi]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Films about stalking]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the Tamil film|the song|Oru Kal Oru Kannadi (song)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Oru Kal Oru Kannadi\n| image          = OKOK.jpg\n| alt            = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[M. Rajesh]]\n| producer       = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]]\n| writer         = M. Rajesh\n| starring       = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]] <br />[[Hansika Motwani]]<br />[[Narayan Lucky]]<br />[[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]]<br />[[Jangiri Madhumitha]]\n| music          = [[Harris Jayaraj]]\n| cinematography = [[Balasubramaniem]]\n| editing        = [[Vivek Harshan]]\n| studio         = [[Red Giant Movies]]\n| distributor    = [[Red Giant Movies]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2012|4|13|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 166 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|130|m|year=2012}}<ref name=\"Sify\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil-cinema-2012-half-yearly-report-jan-1-june-30-news-tamil-mhhsLzccaaa.html |title=Tamil Cinema 2012- Half Yearly Report (Jan 1-June 30)|publisher=Sify |date=2012-07-07 |accessdate=2012-11-09}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|420|m|year=2012}}<ref name=\"Sify\" />\n}}\n\n'''''Oru Kal Oru Kannadi''''' ({{lit|One Stone, One Mirror}}) abbreviated as '''''OKOK''''' is a [[Tamil films of 2012|2012]] [[Tamil language|Tamil]] [[romantic comedy]] film written and directed by [[M. Rajesh]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Anupama Subramanian DC chennai |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/udhay%E2%80%99s-new-look-okok-912 |title=Udhay\u2019s new look in OKOK |publisher=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |date=2011-03-23 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> It stars producer [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]], in his acting debut, [[Hansika Motwani]] and [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]], whilst featuring [[Harris Jayaraj]]'s music and [[Balasubramaniem]]'s cinematography.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-17/news-interviews/28374647_1_harris-jayaraj-music-romantic-flick Jayaraj to give music for Rajesh's OKOK&nbsp;\u2013 Times Of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2011-01-17). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> The film was named after [[Oru Kal Oru Kannadi (song)|a song]] from the film ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'' (2009). Releasing on 13 April 2012, it opened to highly positive reviews and became a blockbuster.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-22/news-interviews/31378800_1_hansika-fee-oru-kal-oru-kannadi Hansika hikes her fee to 75 lakhs&nbsp;\u2013 Times Of India]. Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2012-04-22). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref><ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-22/news-interviews/31373320_1_tamil-bollywood-debut-film Oru Kal Oru Kannadi to be remade in Bollywood&nbsp;\u2013 Times Of India]. Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2012-04-22). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref><ref name=\"behindwoods1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-movies-may-14/oru-kal-oru-kannadi.html |title=Oru Kal Oru kannadi&nbsp;\u2014 Behindwoods.com&nbsp;\u2014 Tamil Top Ten Movies&nbsp;\u2014 Kalakalappu Vazhakku En 18/7 Leelai Ooh La La La Mattuthavani Mye Oru kal Oru kannadi Asthamanam Mazhaikalam 3 Karnan Meeravudan Krishnan Sooriya Nagaram Nandha Nandhitha Sevarkodi Naanga Aravaan Kaattu Puli Udumban Kadhalil Sodhapuvadhu Yeppadi Muppozhudhum Un Karpanaigal Mouna Guru kollaikaran Vettai Nanban Osthe Rajapattai Uchithanai Mukarnthal Mouna Guru Mambattiyan Velayudham 7aum Arivu Porali Mayakkam Enna |publisher=Behindwoods |date= |accessdate=2012-08-05}}</ref> It was eventually released in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''OK OK'' on 31 August 2012.\n\n== Plot ==\nOne morning in his house, Saravanan receives his ex-girlfriend Meera's wedding invitation. He and his friend Paarthasarathy aka Paartha leave for [[Pondicherry]] to attend the wedding via car. ''En route'', Saravanan recollects his past: He was a ruthless youth working in a film theatre with Paartha. He lives with his parents; his father, Varadharajan, who is educated and works as a college professor and his mother, Shenbagam, who is uneducated and is trying to pass an exam, just to get her college degree. One day in traffic, he sees Meera, a girl training to be an air hostess and [[Love at first sight|falls for her on site]]. He follows her to a cloth shop and also to her Air Hostess class. He saw her house and he and Partha go to her house, as Meera calls them. There, Meera threatens Saravanan by showing her father's photo, who is a Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), Mahendra Kumar. But still, Saravanan follows her and asks her to love him. Meera takes him to Mahendra Kumar's office and he asks Saravanan to stop following Meera. Meera tells Saravanan that she has some qualifications required by her lover like shaving regularly, dressing well, breaking his friendship with Paartha, coming on time, etc.  Saravanan tells this to Partha and Partha asks him if he or Meera is best for him. Saravanan tells him Meera is more important to him than Paartha, causing a break between Saravanan's and Paartha's friendship.\n\nLater, Saravanan joins Paartha's broken love and asks him to rejoin his love. Partha agrees and then they go to [[Mumbai]], following Meera in a flight. There, Meera alas tells him that she loves Saravanan. After some months, Meera calls Saravanan once, but he does not pick up the phone and tells Paartha that Meera is not his real love and it is all nothing, but a drama. But, he really said that for fun. But, Paartha had accidentally switched on the phone while Saravanan told him all this. Meera, mistaking him for intentionally misusing her, comes there and breaks their love. Now, at Pondicherry, during Meera's marriage, both Saravanan and Partha end up drunk and tell a small story, in a comical way describing the broken love of Saravanan and Meera. Just as the marriage is going to happen, Rajini Murugan, a local don, comes there with a pregnant girl and his girlfriend and reveals that Meera's groom has a girlfriend, who is pregnant by him and that the girl Rajini Murugan is with, is that girl. The groom admits to his mistake and reunites with his old girlfriend. Saravanan and Paartha walk off the marriage hall, just then Meera comes and hugs Saravanan, hence reuniting with him.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]] as Saravanan\n* [[Hansika Motwani]] as Meera\n* [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]] as Paartha\n* [[Narayan Lucky]] as Sanjay, Meera's Fianc\u00e9\n* [[Saranya Ponvannan]] as Shenbagam\n* [[Azhagam Perumal]] as Varadharajan\n* [[Sayaji Shinde]] as DC Mahendrakumar\n* [[Uma Padmanabhan]] as Gayathri\n* [[Jangiri Madhumitha]] as Jangiri\n* [[Swaminathan]] as Ulundurpettai Ulaganantha\n* [[Mahanadi Shankar]] as Traffic Police\n*[[Arya (actor)|Arya]] as Rajini Murugan (special appearance)\n* [[Andrea Jeremiah]] as Rajini Murugan's girlfriend [special appearce]\n* [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Jennifer (special appearance)\n* [[Dinesh Kumar (choreographer)|Dinesh Kumar]] (special appearance in the song \"Kadhal Oru\")<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xAfHFFi0O6E |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2014 Kaadhal Oru Video Udhayanidhi, Hansika |publisher=Youtube |date=16 December 2014 |accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nUdhayanidhi Stalin had bought the distribution rights of Rajesh's previous film ''[[Boss Engira Bhaskaran]]''.<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58980.html Red Giant acquires Boss Engira Bhaskaran&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil Movie News]. IndiaGlitz (2010-07-29). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> As the film emerged successful, Udhayanidhi decided to continue the collaboration, going on to play the lead role in the new project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chennai365.com/news/udhayanidhi-is-the-hero-for-director-rajesh/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=12 April 2012 |url-status=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100811210306/http://chennai365.com/news/udhayanidhi-is-the-hero-for-director-rajesh/ |archivedate=11 August 2010 }}. chennai365.com. June 2, 2010</ref>\n\nDuring the pre-production stage,  several actresses including [[Asin Thottumkal]] and [[Nayantara]] were approached to play the female lead but [[Hansika Motwani]] was eventually signed. The protagonist was revealed to be an unemployed youngster, as unofficial reports of a ticket collector and a band master were brushed aside.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/64612.html |title=Who is Udhayanidhi in 'OK OK'? |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-03-07 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] and [[Andrea Jeremiah]] were roped in to perform cameo roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/69565.html |title=Arya to do a cameo |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-08-08 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> Hansika was forced to learn [[Tamil language|Tamil]], for the director wanted her to speak fluently in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/73418.html |title=Hansika masters Tamil? |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-11-02 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> Rajesh planned to retain the same crew members from his first two ventures but since Udhayanidhi wanted [[Harris Jayaraj]] to score the music for his debut film, he was signed over Rajesh's usual associate [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], while the makers decided to proceed with Balasubramaniam as the cinematographer as [[Sakthi Saravanan]] was unavailable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-11-02/ok-ok-rajesh-08-03-11.html |title=Okok Shoot To Commence |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-03-08 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nA photo shoot for the film was held in February 2011 with the lead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-11-01/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-rajesh-07-02-11.html |title= Hansika OK OK |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-02-07 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> The shooting of the film began in March 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/64907.html |title=It's shooting time for 'OKOK' |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-03-16 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref> Filming was held in [[Tidel Park]] and [[Old Mahabalipuram Road|Rajiv Gandhi Road]] in [[Chennai]] on 26 April. The car in which they drive to pondicherry was modified with power steering and other interesting elements. A pondicherry bar was setup in woodlands hotel campus.  In the song Azhage, which was totally shot in dubai, in between bgms were recreated in VGP beach and matched by art director [[Jacki]].<ref>[http://www.sify.com/movies/rajesh-s-nanbenda-becomes-okok-news-tamil-lbsjuleeaej.html?scategory=tamil Rajesh's Nanbenda becomes OKOK]. Sify.com (2011-01-19). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> Overseas shooting locations included Jordan and [[Abu Dhabi]], where the film's team flew over to shoot a song in December 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/okok-team-flies-to-jordan-news-tamil-lmriPSiebde.html |title=OKOK team flies to Jordan |publisher=[[Sify]] |date=2011-12-17 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-11-04/udayanidhi-stalin-oru-kal-oru-kannadi-27-12-11.html |title=Ok Ok Dubai Schedule Completed |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-12-27 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> Some shots were canned at the PVR theater in Ampa Mall, Aminjikarai. Hansika Motwani and Saranya were spotted doing a scene together in the theater.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-11-04/okok-udhayanidhi-stalin-28-03-11.html |title=Hansika Motwani Spotted At Pvr Theaters |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-03-28 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> In the second schedule, director Rajesh shot a scene on Udayanidhi Stalin, Azhagam Perumal and Saranya Ponvannan at [[KK Nagar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/may-11-03/udayanidhi-stalin-hansika-motwani-21-05-11.html |title=Ok Ok Shooting Wrapped Up |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-05-21 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> During a schedule, Santhanam was hospitalized due to illness, delaying the shoot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-11-01/santhanam-okok-05-04-11.html |title=Santhanam Is Possessed! |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-04-05 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]]. Oru Kal Oru Kannadi was released on 13 April 2012 in Tamil as a [[Tamil New Year]] release and on 31 August 2012 in Telugu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.moviegalleri.net/2012/03/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-movie-release-date-on-april-13th-friday.html |title=OKOK Movie Release date on April 13th}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Oru Kal Oru Kannadi\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Harris Jayaraj]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|4 March 2012}}\n| recorded   = 2012\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 25:35\n| language   = [[Tamil (language)|Tamil]]\n| label      = [[Sony Music India]]\n| producer   = Harris Jayaraj\n| prev_title = [[Nanban (2012 film)|Nanban]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Maattrraan]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n}}\n\nThe album features five songs,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/78907.html |title='OKOK' track details |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-03-05 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> composed by [[Harris Jayaraj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-11-04/ok-ok-rajesh-25-02-11.html |title=On Harris Replacing Yuvan |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-02-25 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> The composing sessions took place in [[Singapore]] and [[Ooty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/64808.html |title=Harris in Singapore. OKOK |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2011-03-12 |accessdate=2011-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/mar-11-02/okok-udhayanidhi-stalin-12-03-11.html |title=Harris Jeyaraj In Singapore |publisher=Behindwoods |date=2011-03-12 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> The audio launch was held at the Sathyam Cinemas on 4 March 2012. Actors Karthi, Surya, Jeeva and Arya were present at the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/78955.html |title=Suriya unveils 'Oru Kal Oru Kannadi' music |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-03-06 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> A three-minute trailer and song sequences was screened for the guests and media people as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamil.oneindia.in/movies/news/2012/02/okok-music-from-march-5-aid0136.html |title=OKOK music from March 5 &#124; \u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd 5-\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b87\u0b9a\u0bc8!&nbsp;\u2013 Oneindia Tamil |publisher=Tamil.oneindia.in |date= |accessdate=2012-02-23}}</ref>\n\nThe soundtrack received generally positive reviews. Behindwoods.com claimed that it \"definitely has a few like-able singalongs to keep the audio outlets happy\", providing a rating of 3/5.<ref>[http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-music-reviews/review-1/mar-12-01/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-music-review.html Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Music Review&nbsp;\u2013 Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Music Review]. Behindwoods.com. Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> The Song Venam Machan Venam became an Instant hit and topped the chart for several weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.paatuvarigal.com/2015/01/venam-machan-venam-song-lyrics-from-oru.html|title=Venam Machan Venam Song Lyrics from Oru Kal Oru Kannadi|work=Paatuvarigal \u2013 Tamil Song Lyrics|access-date=2018-05-30}}</ref> Indiaglitz.com mentioned that the composer had \"fulfilled the director's expectations, as the songs strike a chord during the first-listen itself. 'Oru Kal Oru Kannadi' music album celebrates love and reflects youngsters, like the previous films of Rajesh.\"<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/12922.html Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Music Review songs lyrics]. IndiaGlitz (2012-03-07). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref>\n\n\n{{track listing\n| extra_column     = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics       = [[Na. Muthuk