   = 5:09\n| title5        = Vaddura Maavaa\n| extra5        = Naresh Iyer, Velmurugan\n}}\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Critical reception ===\n''Oru Kal Oru Kannadi'' received positive reviews and became a blockbuster at the box office. ''[[Sify]] ''called it a \"rollicking comedy\", stating: \"If all you're looking for is a relaxed time at the movies, then, this is Good Fun. Go with your buddies,  you'll laugh till you have tears in your eyes\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi is Rollicking comedy|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-review-tamil-14996316.html|publisher=Sify |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' rated it 3.5 out of 5 and said: \"M Rajesh is a rarity in Tamil cinema. How else does one explain sitting through almost a three-hour-long movie without realising the passage of time?\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Oru-Kal-Oru-Kannadi/movie-review/12659866.cms |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Review |publisher=[[The Times of India]] |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}{{Rating|3.5|5}}</ref> ''IndiaGlitz'' said \"Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2013 Humour At Its Best!\" and wrote that it was a \"clean and convincing film that makes you laugh every minute\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/12922.html |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2013 Humour At Its Best! |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> ''Behindwoods.com'' rated the film 3 out of 5, stating: \"OKOK double OK\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/apr-12-02/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-review.html |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Review |publisher=Behindwoods |date= |accessdate=14 April 2012}}{{Rating|3|5}}</ref> Oneindia stated that the film \"may not have a great storyline, but watching the film is worth every penny\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/reviews/2012/oru-kal-oru-kannadi-review-140412.html |title=Oru Kal Oru Kannadi&nbsp;\u2013 Review |publisher=Oneindia |date=|accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref> Rohit Ramachandran of Nowrunning.com stated that it was \"by no means a meaningful film experience, but it is a portal for popcorn escapism\".<ref>[http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/8703/tamil/oru-kal-oru-kannadi/3665/review.htm Oru Kal Oru Kannadi Review&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil Movie Review by Rohit Ramachandran]. Nowrunning.com (2012-04-14). Retrieved on 2012-05-08.</ref> Pavithra Srinivasan from [[Rediff.com]] rated it 2 out of 5 and said: \"''OKOK'' is a slightly torturous friendship story of two guys and that's pretty much it\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-oru-kal-oru-kannaadi-is-tortuous/20120413.htm |title=Review: Oru Kal, Oru Kannaadi is tortuous&nbsp;|publisher=Rediff|date=|accessdate=14 April 2012}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n=== Box Office ===\n''Oru Kal Oru Kannadi'' opened in more than 300 screens, with an average of 95 per cent theatre occupancy in urban regions.<ref name=\"behindwoods1\" /> The film began to collect even larger sums of revenue in the next four continuous weeks, acquiring a total of {{INR}}15.09 crore in a matter of 25 days in [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"behindwoods1\" /><ref name=\"indiaglitz1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/82110.html |title=Karthi&nbsp;\u2014 Kajal team up again? - Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=2012-05-14 |accessdate=2012-08-05}}</ref> The film claimed top spot for more than a month at the Chennai box office. Trade pundits declared the film's collections as impressive.<ref name=\"behindwoods1\" /><ref name=\"indiaglitz1\" /><ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-23/news-interviews/31386464_1_comedy-films-scripts-rights | work=The Times Of India | title=OK OK remake rights becomes hot}}</ref> Taken with a budget of {{INR}}13 crore it grossed around {{INR}}42 crore worldwide.<ref name=\"Sify\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|2359201}}\n\n{{M. Rajesh}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Tamil film scores by Harris Jayaraj]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Chennai]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Puducherry]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Dubai]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Jordan]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Abu Dhabi]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Films about stalking]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,MOS:HEADCAPS", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oru_Kal_Oru_Kannadi"}
